                        <foreign>ይወርድ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ በላዕለ፡ ኅብ(ስ)ቱ፡ ወወ(ይ)ኑ፡ ሶበ፡ ይብ፡ ካህን፡ ጸጋ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፈኑ፡<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                      </desc>

                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 1, 3 (partially erased or worn), 4–13; not on quires 2 and 14
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#5v #6v #16v #18r #32v" facs="006 007 017 018 033">folss. 5v, 6v, 16v, 18r, 32v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#7v #13v #26r #34v #37v" facs="008 014 026 035 038">7v, 13v, 26r, 34v, 37v, </locus>, etc.);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#18r #32r #119r #120r #129v" facs="018 032 119 120 130">18r, 32r, 119r, 120r, 129v, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#9v #25r #51r" facs="010 025 051">9v, 25r, 51r</locus>).
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                      Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size.
                      But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout).
                      This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#2v #4v #23v #34v" facs="003 005 024 035">fols. 2v, 4v, 23v, 34v</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
